{
  "texts": [
    "Investing in local energy resources is not always a profitable proposition: buildings have to invest in over-capacity generation to meet peak loads, and storage might only be used for peak shaving on a few days in a month or a few hours in a day.",
    "If these resources can be shared across multiple users, their utilization levels can increase which can further incentivize investment in clean energy sources.",
    "One way to facilitate such sharing is through local energy markets, where prosumers can trade energy with each other before procuring the aggregate balance from an outside source, such as the utility (Agwan, 2020).",
    "There are two main challenges that come up while organizing local energy markets: selecting prosumers to form a market, and then managing the trades within the market.",
    "ML methods are used in tackling both of these."
  ]
}